ogical obstruction to the existence of pseudo-split forms. Constructions based on regular degenerate quadratic forms and new techniques with central extensions provide insight into new phenomena in characteristic 2, which also leads to simplifications of the earlier work. A generalized standard construction is shown to account for all possibilities up to mild central extensions.The results and methods developed in Classification of Pseudo-reductive Groups will interest mathematicians and graduate students who work with algebraic groups in number theory and algebraic geometry in positive characteristic.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aGeometry, Algebraic. 0aGroup theory. 0aLinear algebraic groups. 7aMATHEMATICS / Mathematical Analysis.2bisacsh  a"ient homomorphism.  aCartan k-subgroup.  aDynkin diagram.  aIsogeny Theorem.  aIsomorphism Theorem.  aLevi subgroup.  aSeveriЂrauer variety.  aTits classification.  aTits-style classification.  aWeil restriction.  aalgebraic geometry.  aautomorphism functor.  aautomorphism scheme.  aautomorphism.  acanonical central extensions.  acentral "ient.  acentral extension.  acharacteristic 2.  aconformal isometry.  adegenerate quadratic form.  adouble bond.  aexotic construction.  afield-theoretic invariant.  ageneralized exotic group.  ageneralized standard group.  ageneralized standard presentation.  ageneralized standard.  aisomorphism class.  aisomorphism.  aisotropic group.  ak-tame central extension.  alinear isomorphism.  alinear-algebraic invariant.  amaximal torus.  aminimal type.  anon-reduced root system.  anumber theory.  apseudo-isogeny.  apseudo-reductive group.  apseudo-semisimple group.  apseudo-simple group.  apseudo-simple k-group.  apseudo-split form.  apseudo-split.  aqua